ore emit. The claim Finalized witness signals FinalizeReward dispatch arm has applied (state_root advanced past R_0), so the subsequent `emit_system_tx` captures the post-FinalizeReward state_root → no StaleParent L4.E race. Prior R1 helper polled only task_markets_t (which is unchanged by FinalizeReward); smoke evidence `handover/evidence/stage_b3_smoke_b2_20260511T012401Z/deepseek-v4-flash/seed1/rep1/P002_aime_1983_p2/runtime_repo/rejections.jsonl:9` showed `tx_kind:EventResolve public_summary:stale_parent_root` — the B2 transition was rejected at apply time, leaving task_markets_t.state unchanged at Open and the CPMM lifecycle gap §3.3 not actually closed. R2 fix is binding-tested by `tests/constitution_n2_event_resolve.rs::sg_n2_b2_9_adapter_polls_claim_finalized_before_emit_r2`. Predecessor TB-N2 B2 R1 hash 18bc199e superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N2 B2 (2026-05-11): added `tb_n2_emit_event_resolve_after_finalize` poll-then-emit helper (mirrors `tb8_emit_finalize_after_verify` pattern). Polls `q_snapshot` until task_markets_t[task_id].state == Open; emits `SystemEmitCommand::EventResolve` via `Sequencer::emit_system_tx`. Best-effort contract: Ok(true) on emit / Ok(false) on poll-budget-expiry or task already resolved / Err on unexpected emit_system_tx error. Closes the CPMM lifecycle automation gap from the OMEGA-Confirm exit path. Predecessor hash 48da399a superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.3 (2026-05-05; architect umbrella charter §2 Atom 2.3 — CompleteSetRedeem env-var trigger): ADDITIVE — added make_real_complete_set_redeem_signed_by(keypairs, parent_state_root, event_task, owner, outcome, share_units, suffix, timestamp_logical) helper. Mirrors make_real_complete_set_mint_signed_by shape: builds CompleteSetRedeemTx + canonical-digest + agent-sign via AgentKeypairRegistry. Sole caller is the FORCE_REDEEM env-var hook in evaluator.rs (TB-16.x.2.3); no production caller wired yet. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.2.fix.r2 Patch F4 hash c1360a73 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.2.fix.r2 Patch F4 (2026-05-05; doc-only follow-up addressing Codex CHALLENGE E.3 from the .fix Class 3 audit): the prior .fix Patch E docstring referenced a nonexistent `Sequencer::set_current_round_for_test` symbol while explaining the time-unit difference between this helper and tb11_emit_expire_for_eligible. Patch F4 corrects the doc to point at the actual in-tree mutator (the `seed_q_for_challenge` test helper at src/state/sequencer.rs:~4185) and clarifies that no production round-advance mechanism is wired yet. NO behavior change — pure docstring edit; helper signature, eligibility logic, and call surface are unchanged from .fix Patch E. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.2.fix Patch E hash 3e770c4b superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.2.fix Patch E (2026-05-05; tb16_emit_challenge_resolve_for_eligible eligibility-boundary semantic-fix): the original TB-16.x.2.2 helper used `if elapsed <= window_delta_logical_t { continue; }` — i.e. require elapsed > delta. With delta=0 the helper required ≥1 round to pass, contradicting its own docstring claim "delta=0 makes every Open case immediately eligible". Smoke r3 (post-Patch-A) showed FORCE_CHALLENGE_RESOLVE batch returning count=0 because q.q_t.current_round is NOT auto-advanced per-tx (unlike tb11_emit_expire_for_eligible's caller-supplied current_logical_t which auto-advances per-tx); the OMEGA-Confirm path opens the case and scans within the same round, so elapsed=0 for delta=0 was always skipped. Patch E flips the boundary to `if elapsed < window_delta_logical_t { continue; }` (require elapsed >= delta), aligning impl with docstring. Sole callers of this helper today are the FORCE_-prefixed arena hooks; no production caller depends on the prior off-by-one boundary. Docstring updated to reflect `>= delta` and to clarify the time-unit difference vs tb11. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.2 hash a9bbb1ac superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.2 (2026-05-05; architect umbrella charter §2 Atom 2.2 — ChallengeResolve via challenge-window scheduler): ADDITIVE — added tb16_emit_challenge_resolve_for_eligible(seq, window_delta_logical_t, default_resolution) helper. Mirrors tb11_emit_expire_for_eligible shape: scan economic_state_t.challenge_cases_t for entries with status=Open AND q.q_t.current_round - case.opened_at_round > window_delta; emit ChallengeResolveTx via emit_system_tx (SystemEmitCommand::ChallengeResolve) for each eligible case. Returns (count, bonds_released_micro). emit_system_tx for ChallengeResolve does NOT pre-check case existence/status (sequencer.rs:2590 — construction is unconditional); dispatch-time AlreadyResolved/ChallengeNotFound surfaces as L4.E rejection, not Err here. Predecessor TB-16 Atom 7 R1 Step 3 hash 3390205f superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16 Atom 7 R1 Step 3 (2026-05-04; architect §7.3 FR-16.3 + FR-16.4): ADDITIVE — added 3 real-signature constructors for arena drivers: make_real_challengetx_signed_by (ChallengeTx; FR-16.3), make_real_market_seed_signed_by (MarketSeedTx; FR-16.4), make_real_complete_set_mint_signed_by (CompleteSetMintTx; FR-16.4). Mirror existing make_real_worktx_signed_by / make_real_verifytx_signed_by patterns. No behavior change to existing helpers. Predecessor TB-11 Atom 4 hash dcdb2566 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-11 Atom 4 (2026-05-02; architect §6.2 ruling): added tb11_emit_terminal_summary_for_run + tb11_emit_expire_for_eligible runtime helpers. Mirror tb8_emit_finalize_after_verify pattern; thin wrappers over Sequencer::emit_system_tx with policy-gated eligibility scan for TaskExpire (state ∈ {Open, Bankrupt} + opened_at_logical_t deadline elapsed + no Finalized claim). Predecessor TB-10 Atom 1 hash 403ff876 superseded.
