sed by audit_assertions::assert_44_attempt_telemetry_retrievable_from_cas + assert_45_lean_result_retrievable_from_cas to walk all AttemptTelemetry / LeanResult CAS objects per FR-18R.7 / SG-18R.7. Pure-additive helper over in-memory index; no disk I/O. Class 3 surface (cas/store.rs is NOT in CLAUDE.md STEP_B restricted list). Predecessor TB-18R R4 hash 2d7fd4d5 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R4 (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R4_STEP_B_invariant.md §3 + §4): NEW pub fn `count_by_object_type(&self, ty: ObjectType) -> u64` — counts CAS objects whose metadata `object_type` matches. Used by chain_derived_run_facts::compute_run_facts_from_chain_with_invariant to populate attempt_aborted_count (FR-18R.4 v2 — count of TerminalAbortRecord CAS objects per run). Pure-additive helper over the in-memory index; no disk I/O; no change to put/get/open semantics. Class 3 surface (cas/store.rs is NOT in CLAUDE.md STEP_B restricted list). Predecessor TB-18R R3.fix hash 01884e5b superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R3.fix (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R3FIX_STEP_B_cas_reload.md §2.1 + §3.1): NEW pub fn `reload_index_from_sidecar(&mut self) -> Result<(), CasError>` — re-reads the on-disk `.turingos_cas_index.jsonl` and merges new entries into self.index. Used by long-lived sequencer.cas to pick up writes performed by short-lived evaluator-side CasStore handles on the same disk path. Idempotent. Reuses existing private `load_index_from_sidecar` free function. Pure-additive; no change to existing put/get/open semantics. Class 3 surface (cas/store.rs is NOT in CLAUDE.md STEP_B restricted list — only cas/schema.rs is). Closes the L0-smoke-2026-05-06 split-brain bug where R3 admission helper read sequencer.cas's stale index and fell back to PredicateFailed instead of refining to LeanFailed/SorryBlocked. Predecessor TB-16.x.1 hash 12ce3f35 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.1 (2026-05-04): CasStore::get wraps libgit2 read in worker thread + recv_timeout (